{"parse":{"title":"machine","pageid":7121,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|machiné}}\n==English==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|en|:bor|frm:machine|tree=1}}\n{{bor+|en|frm|machine}}, from {{der|en|la|māchina||a machine, engine, contrivance, device, stratagem, trick}}, from {{der|en|grc-dor|μᾱχᾰνᾱ́}}, cognate with {{cog|grc-att|μηχᾰνή||a machine, engine, contrivance, device}}, from which comes {{m|en|mechanical}}.  Displaced native {{noncog|ang|searu}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/məˈʃiːn/}}\n** {{audio|en|En-uk-machine.ogg|a=UK}}\n** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Naomi Persephone Amethyst (NaomiAmethyst)-machine.wav|a=GA}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-machine.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{rhymes|en|iːn|s=2}}\n* {{hyph|en|ma|chine}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q11019}}A device that directs and controls [[energy]], often in the form of [[movement]] or [[electricity]], to produce a certain effect.\n#* {{quote-journal|en|title=A better waterworks|date=2013-06-01| volume=407| issue=8838| page=5 (Technology Quarterly)| magazine=w:The Economist| url=http://www.economist.com/news/technology-quarterly/21578526-medical-technology-artificial-kidneys-are-getting-closer-becoming-clinical| passage=An artificial kidney these days still means a refrigerator-sized dialysis '''machine'''. Such devices mimic the way real kidneys cleanse blood and eject impurities and surplus water as urine.}}\n# {{lb|en|dated}} A vehicle operated mechanically, such as an [[automobile]] or an [[airplane]].\n#* {{RQ:Burroughs Return of Tarzan|version=Burt|pages=40–41|pageref=41|passage=As he stood directly beneath a brilliant arc light, waiting for a limousine that was approaching to pass him, he heard his name called in a sweet feminine voice. Looking up, he met the smiling eyes of Olga de Coude as she leaned forward upon the back seat of the '''machine'''. He bowed very low in response to her friendly greeting. When he straightened up the '''machine''' had borne her away.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=F. Britten Austin|title=The Air-Scout|journal=The Strand Magazine| location=London| publisher=George Newnes, Ltd.| month=July|year=1914| volume=XLVIII| page=568| pageurl=https://archive.org/stream/TheStrandMagazineAnIllustratedMonthly/TheStrandMagazine1914bVol.XlviiiJul-dec#page/n581/mode/2up| passage=As the aviator turned his '''machine''' to reconnoitre in the new direction, he was surprised to see the hostile aeroplane between him and his objective.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=Franklin W. Dixon|title=The Missing Chums|publisher=w:Grosset & Dunlap|year=1928|page=1|passage=\"Joe, how soon will you be ready to roll?\" Frank Hardy burst into the garage where his brother was working on a sleek, black-and-silver motorcycle. \"Right now, if this '''machine''' kicks over,\" Joe replied, putting down a wrench.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|year=1976|month=August|author=David Laraway|title=Weekends and Other Days: Loving at the edge of life|editor=w:Edith Raymond Locke|journal=[[w:Mademoiselle (magazine)|Mademoiselle]]|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=[[w:Condé Nast|Condé Nast Publications]]|page=256|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/mademoiselle82julnewy/page/n407/mode/1up|columns=1–2|issn=0024-9394|oclc=1715227|passage=Now, here, he is a Racer. He throws his leg over the '''machine''' and settles onto the narrow rubber seat. He pushes it through its revolution twice with his hand, slowly, to force the fuel into the carburetor. Then he stands with his left foot on the peg and jumps down on the lever with his right. The engine starts immediately; he takes very good care of his '''machine'''. He sits down, waiting for it to warm up. He caresses the top of the tank, understanding that the '''machine''' cannot feel the gesture but content that he can.}}\n# {{lb|en|telephony|abbreviation}} An [[answering machine]] or, by extension, [[voice mail]].\n#: {{ux|en|I called you earlier, but all I got was the '''machine'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|computing}} A [[computer]].\n#: {{ux|en|Game developers assume they're pushing the limits of the '''machine'''.}}\n#: {{ux|en|He refuses to turn off his Linux '''machine'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|figuratively}} A person or organisation that seemingly acts like a machine, being particularly [[efficient]], [[single-minded]], or [[unemotional]].\n#: {{ux|en|Bruce Campbell was a \"demon-killing '''machine'''\" because he made quick work of killing demons.}}\n#: {{ux|en|The government has become a money-making '''machine'''.}}\n# Especially, the group that controls a political or similar organization; a combination of persons acting together for a common purpose, with the agencies which they use.\n#* {{RQ:Landor Imaginary Conversations|III|Rousseau and Malesherbes|passage=The whole '''machine''' of government, civil and religious, ought never to bear upon the people with a weight so oppressive}}\n# {{lb|en|poetry}} Supernatural agency in a poem, or a superhuman being introduced to perform some exploit.\n#* {{RQ:Spectator|author=Addison||351|April 21 1712|passage=I am apt to think, that the changing of the Trojan fleet into water-nymphs, which is the most violent '''machine''' in the whole Æneid{{...}}}}\n# {{lb|en|politics|chiefly|US}} The system of [[special interest group]]s that supports a political party, especially in urban areas.\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1902|title=The Friend\n|passage=A '''machine''' politician cannot see why the straight ticket (as he and his clique of party bosses prepare it) should not be voted by every citizen belonging to that party.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2006|author=Jerry F. Hough|title=Changing Party Coalitions: The Mystery of the Red State-blue State Alignment|publisher=Algora Publishing|isbn=9780875864082|page=37\n|passage=In essence, therefore, the right-fork strategy of the Democrats meant an alliance of the South with the political '''machines''' built on the non-Protestant immigrants in key Northeastern states.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2013|author=Paul M. Green; Melvin G. Holli|title=The Mayors: The Chicago Political Tradition, fourth edition|publisher=SIU Press|isbn=9780809331994|page=126\n|passage=He was thrust into a political maelstrom for which he was ill-prepared, and yet he was, most notably, the Chicago '''machine'''&#39;s political savior.}}\n# {{lb|en|euphemistic|obsolete}} [[penis|Penis]].\n#* {{RQ:Cleland Fanny Hill|1|107|He now reſumes his attempts in more form: firſt he put one of the pillows under me, to give the blank of his aim a more favourable elevation, and another under my head, in eaſe of it: then ſpreading my thighs, and placing himſelf ſtanding between them, made them reſt upon his hips: applying then the point of his '''machine''' to the ſlit, into which he ſought entrance;}}\n# {{lb|en|historical}} A contrivance in the Ancient Greek theatre for indicating a change of scene, by means of which a god might cross the stage or deliver a divine message; the [[deus ex machina]].\n# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A [[bathing machine]].\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1823|author=w:Frances Burney|title=Journals and Letters|page=512|publisher=Penguin|year_published=2001\n|passage=One '''Machine''' only was provided for Bathers, the Limitted smoothness of the sands not extending widely enough to admit another.}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* See also [[Thesaurus:machine]]\n\n====Hyponyms====\n{{col4|en|franking machine\n|add value machine\n|cigarette machine\n|excavating machine\n|finite state machine\n|jet machine\n|knitting machine\n|paper machine|grinding machine\n|pinball machine\n|poker machine\n|rowing machine|bean machine\n|sewing machine|machine that goes \"ping\"\n|simple machine|c-machine|choice machine|ice resurfacing machine|o-machine\n|slot machine|a-machine|blister machine|dishwashing machine\n|smoke machine|sounding machine\n|tamping machine| Charpy machine|penny-in-the-slot machine\n|ticket machine\n|tunnel boring machine|Google machine|interlingual machine translation|liquid state machine|nondeterministic Turing machine|watch timing machine|watch-timing machine||machine intelligence\n|vending machine|interactive teller machine\n|virtual machine\n|washing machine\n|welding machine|brain machine|Eilenberg machine|mind machine|sound machine|white noise machine\n}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col4|en|machine politics|machine-hour|machine age\n|goal machine|Hollerith machine|orphan-crushing machine|sanding machine\n|machine gun\n|machinegun\n|machine-made\n|machine-readable\n|Machine Spirit|wash machine|wash-machine\n|roller machine\n|machine-washable\n|machine bolt|antimachine|biomachine|femtomachine|fuckmachine|infomachine|intermachine|machinability|machinable|machineability|machineable|machineful|machineless|machinelike|machinely|machineman|machinic|machinify|machinima|machinism|machinize|megamachine|metamachine|micromachine|mismachine|multimachine|nanomachine|nonmachine|premachine|remachine|snowmachine|submachine|supermachine|turbomachine|machine lace|lace machine\n|machine code\n|machine cycle\n|deus ex machina\n|machinate\n|machination\n|machine-paced|lag machine|machine washable\n|machine room\n|machine instruction\n|machine language\n|machine learning\n|machine of government\n|machine pistol\n|machine screw\n|machine shop\n|machine word\n|machine tool\n|machine translation\n|accounting machine|adding machine|ATM machine|Atwood machine|automated machine learning|automated teller machine|automatic data processing machine|automatic teller machine|baby machine|ball machine|bank machine|bread machine|carding machine|cash machine|coffee machine|compound machine|copy machine|cornucopia machine|dance machine|data processing machine|deflavorizing machine|dictation machine|ditto machine|Ditto machine|drum machine|drying machine|DVD-R machine|dynamo-electric machine|Enigma machine|epsilon-machine|exercise machine|fax machine|finite-state machine|fire machine|flying machine|fog machine|forest machine|forestry machine|fruit machine|fucking machine|gaming machine|ghost in the machine|ground effect machine|ground-effect machine|gumball machine|Harvard machine|heart-lung machine|hug machine|ice machine|infernal machine|Jacquard machine|karaoke machine|laugh machine|light machine gun|light machine guns|little brown fucking machine|love machine|machine elf|machine gunner|machine operator|machine politician|machine wash|machine-gunner|machine-translate|machine-wash|man-machine|Mealy machine|milking machine|milling machine|money machine|Moore machine|mud machine|oracle machine|perpetual motion machine|perpetual motion machine of the first kind|perpetual motion machine of the second kind|poker machine|pokie machine|political machine|poop machine|praying machine|rasping machine|reverse vending machine|reversing machine|road machine|rod machine|rope machine|rotor machine|rubbing machine|Rube Goldberg machine|screw machine|scrum machine|scrummaging machine|seaming machine|sex machine|sex-machine|slabbing machine|slotting machine|Smith machine|snow machine|soda machine|splining machine|squeeze machine|stack machine|state machine|step machine|support vector machine|tabulating machine|tape machine|tattoo machine|telephone answering machine|thinking machine|threshing machine|ticket stamping machine|ticket vending machine|ticket-stamping machine|time machine|Tipler machine|Tipler time machine|trowel machine|Turing machine|universal Turing machine|unlimited register machine|virtual machine monitor|von Neumann machine|voting machine|war machine|wayback machine|weighing machine|well-oiled machine|wetting machine|wheeling machine|wind machine|winnowing machine|xerox machine|Zeno machine|zipper machine\n|machinery\n|mechanic\n|mechanical\n|mechanism\n|mechanistic|arcwall machine|Atwood's machine|bookkeeping machine|business machine|claw machine|influence machine|kidney machine|machine epsilon|machine head|machine zone|mean machine|office machine|photo machine|sleep machine|spin machine|Wimshurst machine\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|ain|マシン|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|bn|মেশিন|bor=1}}\n* {{d