\n* German: {{t+|de|Maschine|f}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|μηχανή|f}}, {{t+|el|μηχανισμός|m}}, {{t+|el|μηχάνημα|n}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|μηχανή|f}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|μαχανά|f}}\n* Gujarati: {{t+|gu|યંત્ર|n}}, {{t|gu|મશીન}}\n* Haitian Creole: {{t|ht|machin}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|מְכוֹנָה|f|tr=m'khoná}}\n* Hiligaynon: {{t|hil|makina}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|यंत्र|m}}\n* Hmong:\n*: White Hmong: {{t|mww|tshuab}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|gép}}, {{t+|hu|szerkezet}}, {{t+|hu|masina}}\n* Hunsrik: {{t|hrx|Maschin|f}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|vél|f}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|mesin}}, {{t+|id|sawat}}\n* Ingrian: {{t|izh|mašina}}, {{t|izh|kapine}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|meaisín|f}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|macchina|f}}, {{t+|it|meccanismo|m}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|機械|tr=きかい, kikai}}, {{t+|ja|マシン|tr=mashin}}, {{t+|ja|器械|tr=きかい, kikai}}\n* Kannada: {{t+|kn|ಯಂತ್ರ}}\n* Kazakh: {{t+|kk|машина}}\n* Khmer: {{t+|km|យន្ត}}, {{t+|km|គ្រឿង}}, {{t+|km|ម៉ាស៊ីន}}\n* Kongo: {{t|kg|masini}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|기계(機械)}}, {{t+|ko|기계(器械)}}, {{t|ko|머신}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{t|ckb|مەکینە}}\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t+|kmr|makîne}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{t+|ky|машина}}\n* Lao: {{t|lo|ເຄື່ອງ}}, {{t+|lo|ກົນ}}, {{t|lo|ກົນຈັກ}}, {{t+|lo|ເຄື່ອງຈັກ}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|māchina|f}}\n* Latvian: {{t|lv|mašīna|f}}, {{t|lv|aparāts|m}}\n* Lingala: {{t|ln|masíni}}, {{t|ln|masini}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t+|lt|mašina|f}}\n* Macedonian: {{t+|mk|ма́шина|f}}, {{t|mk|у́стројство|n}} {{qualifier|mechanism}}\n* Malay: {{t+|ms|mesin}}\n* Malayalam: {{t+|ml|യന്ത്രം}}\n* Maltese: {{t|mt|magna|f}}\n* Māori: {{t+|mi|mīhini}}, {{t|mi|pūrere}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|यंत्र|n}}, {{t|mr|मशीन|n}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t+|mn|машин}}\n*: Mongolian script: {{t|mn|ᠮᠠᠱᠢᠨ}}\n* Neapolitan: {{t|nap|macchena|f}}\n* Norman: {{t|nrf|machinne|f}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t+|nb|maskin|m}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t|nn|maskin|m|f}}\n* Odia: {{t+|or|ଯନ୍ତ୍ର}}\n* Old English: {{t|ang|searu|f}}\n* Pali: {{t|pi|yanta|n}}\n* Pashto: {{t|ps|ماشين|m|tr=māšin}}, {{t+|ps|آله|f|tr=āla}}\n* Persian:\n*: Dari: {{t|prs|مَاشِین}}, {{t|prs|آلَت}}\n*: Iranian Persian: {{t+|fa-ira|ماشین}}, {{t|fa-ira|آلَت}}\n* Plautdietsch: {{t|pdt|Maschien|f}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|maszyna|f}}, {{t+|pl|ustrojstwo|n}} {{qualifier|colloquial, joking}}, {{t+|pl|urządzenie}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|máquina|f}}\n* Punjabi: {{t|pa|ਮਸ਼ੀਨ}}, {{t|pa|ਜੰਤਰ|f}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|mașină|f}}, {{t|ro|mașină electrică|f}}, {{t|ro|mașină mecanică|f}}\n* Romansh: {{t|rm|maschina|f}}, {{qualifier|Sutsilvan}} {{t|rm|maschegna|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|маши́на|f}}, {{t+|ru|механи́зм|m}}, {{t+|ru|аппара́т|m}}, {{t+|ru|устройство|n}} {{qualifier|mehanism}}, {{t+|ru|маши́нка|f}} {{qualifier|of household devices}}\n* Sami:\n*: Northern Sami: {{t|se|mašiidna}}, {{t|se|mášen}}\n* Sanskrit: {{t+|sa|यन्त्र|n}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|inneal|m}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|маши́на|f}}, {{t|sh|стро̑ј|m}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|mašína|f}}, {{t+|sh|strȏj|m}}\n* Sinhalese: {{t|si|යන්ත්රය}}\n* Slovak: {{t+|sk|stroj|m}}, {{t+|sk|mašina|f}} {{qualifier|colloquial}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|stroj|m}}, {{t|sl|mašina|f}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{t|dsb|mašina|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|máquina|f}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|mashine}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|maskin|c}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|makina|f}}, {{t|tl|sigmo}}\n* Tajik: {{t+|tg|мошин}}, {{t|tg|мошина}}, {{t|tg|олат}}, {{t|tg|дастгоҳ}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|எந்திரம்}}\n* Tatar: {{t|tt|машина}}\n* Telugu: {{t+|te|యంత్రము}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|เครื่อง}}, {{t+|th|กล}}, {{t+|th|เครื่องจักร}}\n* Tibetan: {{t|bo|འཕྲུལ་འཁོར}}\n* Tigrinya: {{t|ti|መኪና}}\n* Tumbuka: {{t|tum|makina}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|makine}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|ماكینه|tr=makina}}, {{t|ota|چرخ|tr=çarh}}\n* Turkmen: {{t|tk|maşyn}}, {{t|tk|maşinka}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|маши́на|f}}\n* Urdu: {{t+|ur|آلَہ|m}}, {{t|ur|مَشِین|f}}\n* Uyghur: {{t|ug|ماشىنا}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|mashina}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|máy}}, {{t+|vi|máy móc}}\n* Walloon: {{t+|wa|machene|f}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|peiriant}}, {{t|cy|ermig|m|f}}\n* Yakut: {{t|sah|массыына}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|מאַשין|f}}\n* Zhuang: {{t|za|gihgi}}, {{t|za|gihgai}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|group that controls an organization}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|機構}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|koneisto}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|μηχανισμός|m}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|macchina|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|機構|tr=きこう, kikō}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|기구(機構)}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|маши́на|f}}, {{t+|ru|аппара́т|m}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|archaic: vehicle, automobile}}\n* Amharic: {{t|am|መኪና}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|auto|m}}, {{t+|ca|automòbil|m}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|mašina|f}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|automobiel|m}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|automobiili}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Maschine|f}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|masina}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|otomobil}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|ماشین|tr=mâšin}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|automóvel|m}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|mașină|f}}, {{t+|ro|automobil}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|маши́на|f}}, {{t+|ru|автомоби́ль|m}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|стро̑ј|m}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|strȏj|m}}\n* Slovak: {{t+|sk|mašina|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|coche|m}}\n* Yakut: {{t|sah|массыына}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|a person who is very proficient}}\n* Asturian: {{t+|ast|máquina|f}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|màquina|f}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|stroj|m}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|machine|f}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|kone}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|machine|f}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|máquina|f}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Maschine|f}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|μηχανή|f}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|gapah}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|macchina|f}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|maszyna}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|máquina|f}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|mașină|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|маши́на|f}}\n* Russian: {{t|sh|стро̑ј|m}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|strȏj|m}}\n* Slovak: {{t+|sk|stroj|m}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|máquina|m|f}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|makine}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top|machine}}\n* Ido: {{t+check|io|mashino}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{t-check|ckb|مەکینە}}\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t+check|kmr|makîne|f}}\n* Latin: {{t-check|la|machina|f}}\n* Slovene: {{t+check|sl|stroj|m}} (1,4)\n* Swedish: {{t+check|sv|maskin|c}}\n* Taos: {{t-check|twf|mąkìnoʼóna}}\n* Yiddish: {{t-check|yi|מאַשין|f}}\n* Korean: {{t+check|ko|기기}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====References====\n* {{pedia}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# To make by [[machinery]].\n# To [[shape]] or finish by machinery; {{lb|en|usually, more specifically}} to shape subtractively by metal-cutting with machine-controlled toolpaths.\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=Helmi A. Youssef|title=Machining of Stainless Steels and Super Alloys|year=2015|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=FBfICgAAQBAJ&pg=PA6&dq=%22machining%22&hl=&cd=23&source=gbs_api#v=onepage&q=%22machining%22&f=false|isbn=978-1-118-91936-1|page=6|passage=Engineering materials have been recently developed whose hardness and strength are considerably increased, such that the cutting speed and the MRR tend to fall when '''machining''' such materials using traditional methods like turning, milling, grinding, and so on.}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|en|machinist}}\n* [[machinofacture]]\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|make by machine}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|koneistaa}}, {{t+|fi|työstää}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|usiner}}\n* German: {{t+|de|herstellen}}\n* Greek: {{t|el|επεξεργάζομαι μηχανικά}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|előállít}}, {{t+|hu|gyárt}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t|nb|maskinere}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t|nn|maskinere}}, {{t|nn|maskinera}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|mecanizar}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|shape or finish by machinery}}\n* Czech: {{t|cs|obrábět}}\n* German: {{t+|de|bearbeiten}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|megmunkál}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|meaisínigh}}\n* Japanese: {{t|ja|機械加工する|tr=kikai kakō suru}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t|nb|maskinere}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t|nn|maskinere}}, {{t|nn|maskinera}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|mecanizar}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:Webster 1913}}\n* {{R:Century 1911}}\n* {{R:Greens|id=t7bqhxa|pos=n}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=acehimn|Eichman}}\n\n{{C|en|Genitalia}}\n\n==Dutch==\n{{wp|nl:}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|nl|masjine|masjien||adapted}}\n* {{alt|nl|machien||archaic or colloquial}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|nl|:bor|fr:machine}}\nBorrowed from {{bor|nl|fr|machine}}, from {{der|nl|frm|machine}}, from {{der|nl|la|māchina}}, from {{der|nl|grc-dor|μᾱχανᾱ́}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/mɑˈʃin(ə)/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-machine.ogg}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|ma|chi|ne}}\n* {{rhymes|nl|inə|in}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{nl-noun|f|-s|++,+}}\n\n# {{l|en|machine}} {{gloss|mechanical or electrical device}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|nl\n|broodmachine\n|espressomachine\n|hormachine\n|keukenmachine\n|koffiemachine\n|kopieermachine\n|machinaal\n|machineren\n|naaimachine\n|nietmachine\n|schrijfmachine\n|tunnelboormachine\n|vliegmachine\n|wasmachine\n}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|nl\n|machinatie\n|machinist\n|mechaniek\n|mechanisch\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|af|masjien}}\n* {{desc|jvn|mesin|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ms|mesin|bor=1}}\n** {{desc|id|mesin}}\n** {{desc|su|mesin|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|srn|masyin|bor=1}}\n** {{desc|djk|masini|bor=1}}\n** {{desc|hns|mashin|bor=1}}\n** {{desc|car|masini|bor=1}}\n** {{desc|srm|masíni|bor=1}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|fr|:inh|frm:machine}}\n{{inh+|fr|frm|machine}}, borrowed from {{bor|fr|la|machina||a machine, engine, contrivance, device, stratagem, trick}}, itself a borrowing from Doric {{der|fr|grc|μᾱχᾰνᾱ́}}. Not to be confused with {{m|fr|machin}}, which means \"thing\".\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA}}\n* {{audio|fr|Fr-machine.ogg|text=une machine}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-DenisdeShawi-machine.wav|a=<<Canada>> (<<Shawinigan>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-LoquaxFR-machine.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Poslovitch-machine.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-WikiLucas00-machine.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|f}}\n\n# [[#English|machine]], [[#English|device]] {{rfclarify|fr}}\n# {{lb|fr|figuratively}} [[#English|machine]] {{gloss|combination of persons acting together for a common purpose, with the agencies which they use}}\n#: {{coi|fr|la '''machine''' bureaucratique|}}\n# [[engine]]\n#: {{coi|fr|[[faire machine arrière|faire '''machine''' arrière]]|to [[backpedal]]}}\n#: {{coi|fr|[[machine à vapeur|'''machine''' à vapeur]]|[[steam engine|steam '''engine''']]}}\n#: {{coi|fr|[[salle des machines|salle des '''machines''']]|[[engine room|'''engine''' room]]}}\n# {{lb|fr|slang}} [[#English|machine]] {{gl|a person who is very efficient}}\n#: {{ux|fr|Ce type, c'est une vraie '''machine'''!| What a guy, he's a real machine!}}\n# {{lb|fr|Quebec|Acadia|dated}} [[car]]\n#: {{syn|fr|voiture|char}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col4|fr\n|code machine\n|langage machine\n|faire une machine\n\n|machine à boule\n|machine à café\n|machine à coudre\n|machine à écrire\n|machine à explorer le temps\n|machine à laver\n|machine à plastifier\n|machine à sous\n\n|machine à voyager dans le temps\n|machine de Turing\n|machine virtuelle\n\n}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|fr\n|machinal\n|machination\n|machiner\n|machinerie\n|machinisme\n|machiniste}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|fr\n\n|mécanique\n|mécanisme\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n{{top3}}\n* {{desc|am|ማሽን|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|gcf|machin}}\n* {{desc|az|maşın|bor=1}}\n* {{desctree|da|maskine|bor=1}}\n* {{desctree|nl|machine|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|de|Maschine|bor=1}} {{see desc}}\n* {{desc|ht|machin}}\n* {{desc|li|mesjien|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|no|-|bor=1}} {{l|nb|maskin}}\n* {{desc|ps|ماشين|tr=māšín|bor=1}}\n* {{desctree|fa|ماشین|tr=mâšin|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ro|mașină|bor=1}} {{q|also via German}}\n* {{desc|es|mashina|bor=1}} {{q|Louisiana}}\n* {{desc|sv|maskin|bor=1}}\n* {{desctree|tg|мошин|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|eo|maŝino|bor=1}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{l|fr|chemina}}\n\n==Middle French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|frm|:bor|la:māchina}}\nBorrowed from {{bor|frm|la|māchina}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{frm-noun|f}}\n\n# {{l|en|machine}}; [[device]]\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|fr|machine}} {{see desc}}\n* {{desc|en|machine|bor=1}} {{see desc}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi|etym=1}}\n* {{R:Godefroy|supplement=1}}\n\n==Walloon==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|wa|/ma.ʃin/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{wa-noun|f}}\n\n# {{l|en|machine}}"}}